    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your <strong>leek[s]</strong> in half lengthways, wash thoroughly to remove any grit then top, tail and dice finely</p><p>Trim the ends off your <strong>Brussels sprouts</strong>, then chop in half lengthways and chop your <strong>Tenderstem broccoli</strong> into thirds</p><p>Peel and chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-green-veggie-lasagne/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced leek </strong>to the pan with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook, covered, for 6-7 min or until softened</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-green-veggie-lasagne/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the leek has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for a further 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, remove the pan from the heat and add the <strong>chopped Brussels sprouts </strong>and<strong> chopped Tenderstem broccoli</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 these are your <strong>green veggies</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-green-veggie-lasagne/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat 3 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [4 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> in a pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[4 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms \u2013 this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually whisk 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[525ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> into the roux, a little at a time, and cook for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains \u2013 this is your <strong>b\u00e9chamel sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-green-veggie-lasagne/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the <strong>b\u00e9chamel sauce</strong> from the heat</p><p>Tear your <strong>'Nduja</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) into the b\u00e9chamel sauce</p><p>Add your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> to the pot and whisk everything together until well combined \u2013 this is your <strong>'Nduja b\u00e9chamel</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-green-veggie-lasagne/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Layer 1/3 of the<strong> green veggies </strong>over the bottom of an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong>, top with 1/3 of your <strong>lasagne sheets</strong>, being careful not to overlap the pasta, then top with 1/3<strong> </strong>of the <strong>'Nduja b\u00e9chamel</strong></p><p>Repeat this process until you end up with a final layer of<strong> 'Nduja b\u00e9chamel</strong></p><p>Tip: You may need to layer differently depending on the size of your dish!</p><p>Top with the <strong>grated cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-green-veggie-lasagne/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Put the dish in the oven for 30 min or until the pasta is cooked \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy 'Nduja & green veggie lasagne</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>white wine vinegar\u00a0</strong>with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>\u00a0\u2013 this is your<strong>\u00a0dressing</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once done, remove the dish from the oven and leave to stand for 5 min before serving (this helps the flavours to develop and makes it easier to serve!)</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-nduja-and-green-veggie-lasagne/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy 'Nduja & green veggie lasagne</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>salad</strong> to the side and drizzle over the <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
